<br>
Andlie <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jaranna>Jaranna</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 464<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/17/03 3:31:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1451.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Spirited Away</span><hr size=1> I'll be honest.  Princess Mononoke was so-so for me.  Great animation, decent story, but it was just way too preachy for me.  I don't do preachy.  I get enough of that on Sunday mornings.<br>
<br>
Grave of the Fireflies was good, though.  Not great, but good.  These are the only two Studio Ghibli films I've yet seen.  I want to see the others, but so far I haven't been THAT impressed with them.<br>
<br>
Though I hear Totoro is pretty damn funny. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://webpages.charter.net/thewok/jarasig.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
