<br>
All the characters in Princess Mononoke felt forced.  The characters in his other films all feel much more natural.<br>
<br>
I would disagree w/ you about Grave of Fireflies, as I think that was a great movie (not good <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ).<br>
<br>
It's hard for me to pick a &quot;favorite&quot; from all the Miyazaki films.  In some respects they're all very different from one another.  Laputa: Castle in the Sky is more of an adventure movie.  Porco Rosso is more of a romance.  Nausicaa of the Valley of Wind is more of an ecological moral story.  Spirited away is more a story of learning how to survive &amp; value oneself.<br>
<br>
If I could only own one of them, I'd probably choose either Porco Rosso or Spirited Away, but I love them all (except Princess Mononoke, which is odd, because Miyazaki thinks that one is his best work <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ).<br>
<br>
